{"TopicId":196786,"ForumId":21,"TopicTitle":"Hoverbike, Skycycle, got it","CreatedByName":"lucho","CreatedById":12856,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-08T13:36:07Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"lucho","CreatedById":12856,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-08T13:36:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMost people like to think big: Go big or go home. But how about going small? I \u0027ve designed a small \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003EVTOL\u003C/abbr\u003E. Hoverbike, Skycycle, whatever you call it, it\u0027s small (barely one ton), fast (It can cruise at up to 62 m/s, although ~55 m/s is advised), and with excellent endurance. And it seats two kerbals!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRunning on batteries is how I got it so small. twin rotors and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E wheels keep it stable. Truth is, it\u0027s\u00A0 got more power than you\u0027ll actually need.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n*edit* how do I attach images?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n*edit2* fixed with KerbalX mod\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022OiBdoBU.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002275.00\u0022 height=\u0022900\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/OiBdoBU.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022iIoS9Fl.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002275.00\u0022 height=\u0022900\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/iIoS9Fl.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022e3cxXgs.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002275.00\u0022 height=\u0022900\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/e3cxXgs.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere\u0027s the lowrider on KerbalX:\u00A0 \u003C